history.content: I'm taking 70 with 61C right now and its doable. The projects are pretty constant and are a pain so they will definitely take some of your time away from doing 70 homework. I don't have to deal with the pressure of declaring so that takes some of the stress for me. It is doable, but I know you have to  do well in 70 so its really up to you.

children.subject: This sounds like a reasonable schedule. I really recommend looking over all the 70 and 61C material during winter break, so it won't be the first time you're seeing it next semester (I personally found the post-MT2 material to be the hardest in 70, but I much prefer discrete math to probability).

history.content:
Hello, I'm currently an undeclared L&S sophomore. I took CS70 this semester but I had to drop the class because I didn't do too well on the second midterm. I want to finish lower divs by next semester so that I can focus on upper division classes starting junior year. I'm familiar with the materials up to the second midterm so I'm not TOO worried about 70. But I've heard 61C is pretty tough so I'm wondering if I should take 70 with 61C or not. Any opinions?

(I got an A- in 61A and currently on route for B+ in 61B, therefore will need B or higher for CS70.)
history.subject: 70 + 61C + Breadth
